data.description: For more information & showings contact Megan with Thomas Realty @ 864-270-2387! Welcome to 124 Oaks Court in the lovely Griffin Oaks community! This quaint neighborhood has highlighted the natural beauty of the area by keeping surrounding trees & plants for a wooded, private feeling. It's hard not to love the neighborhood as you drive through it! This unique location provides privacy, with easy access to towns & larger cities. Located at the Pickens/Easley line, down the road from the Pickens Country Club golf course. If you're curious about the location, Pickens is located at the base of the Blue Ridge Mountains. Featuring a wide range of opportunities for outdoor adventure! Local Mountains, to include the well-known Table Rock State Park, offer a great place for trail hiking, canoeing, ziplining, peaceful picnics & fresh air! Sassafras Mountain, the highest point in South Carolina, is about a 35 minute drive. Maybe you are more of a lake person & you love lake recreation - Lake Keowee, Jocassee & Hartwell can all be reached in around 40 minutes or less! Buy a boat, rent a boat, camp, water ski, swim, paddleboard; the possibilities seem endless! Clemson University is just about 30 mins down the road, imagine a short drive to watch & support your favorite College team play your favorite sports! If you are looking to live in a smaller town, while working in a larger city, then take a closer look! Easy access to Greenville, SC (approx 35 min drive), offering ample opportunity for job selection, all while enjoying a more rural location at home. Easley, Anderson & Seneca can also be quickly accessed. Ashville, NC is approximately 1.5 hours away. If you think the location sounds great, wait until you hear about the property! Sitting on just under a 1 acre lot, this home offers a spacious layout with 4 bedrooms, 3 full bathrooms & 1 half bathroom. Through the front door you will be met with a spacious entryway. The living room features a lovely gas log fireplace. The modern colors, hardwood floors & fireplace make this space very attractive! Living room is open to the kitchen, finished with white cabinets, granite countertops & a subway tile backsplash. Kitchen offers space for barstool seating. This dining room....whew! The dining room measures approximately 19x12 - this space can fit that large farmhouse table that seats the entire family! The master bedroom suite is located on the right side of the home & offers plenty of privacy. Large master, measuring approximately 18x15, boasts a walk-in closet & a private full bathroom. Bathroom has a tub/shower setup & a double sink vanity. To the left side of the home is an extra large great room - this room will wow you! Beautiful wood burning fireplace, built-ins & ample natural light make this a very versatile space! The second main floor bedroom & full bathroom are located off of the great room. Full bathroom offers a walk-in shower. At the side entrance of the home, you will find a mudroom & a utility style room, great for storage. Walk-in laundry room, along with half bathroom is located on the main floor. Up the stairs, on the second level, are two additional bedrooms (great size rooms) & a third full bathroom. To the rear of the home is a private backyard. This yard provides an ideal spot for kids to explore & pets to play. Bring over your family & friends for a great backyard barbecue & a fire in a firepit! Relax on the deck & enjoy a cup of coffee & your favorite book. Detached two car garage can truly fit two vehicles. BONUS - there is a car charging station in the garage. This home is located right by the Golf Course, this would be ideal for charging your golf cart (and your electric car!!)
